David Shapiro from Sasfin Securities chose Starbucks as his stock pick of the day. The company has recently opened a 3,000m² shop in China, and this fills Shapiro with optimism. Wayne McCurrie from Ashburton Investments chose “one of the banks” FirstRand or Standard Bank, as both ran at record highs on Wednesday. He feels they are still at reasonable value and can continue to run further. Simon Brown from Just One Lap chose Long4Life. He says that although it was a bit all over the place, the company’s strategy is beginning to pay off. OR LISTEN TO THE FULL SHOW: